posts.name: Noah Blandford
posts.cooked: Which one are we supposed to score into, the manual isn’t clear.

The colors should correlate. The only question i have is this: “Once an ALGAE passes through the PROCESSOR, it rolls past a scoring sensor array and into the opponent’s PROCESSOR AREA. To keep the PROCESSOR clear for scoring, the HUMAN PLAYER can shift scored ALGAE on top of the PROCESSOR where there are designated ALGAE holders” (Pg 28). Does the opponent score the algae that we put in the processer?
Or is it the opposite? Because we give them the ball. So it could be on the side of the alliance??? The opposing alliance’s color and human player should be the same too
is there a link that you can post to page number or somthing?

posts.cooked: From what I saw in the video, red scored into blue and vice versa.

What I understand is that you can score the ALGEA in the PROCESSOR on your side of the field—where the opposing Human Player is located—earning 6 points for you and 4 for them. posts.name: Stephen Ostermiller
posts.cooked:
Section 5.5 of the manual says:

Once an ALGAE passes through the PROCESSOR, it rolls past a scoring sensor array and into the opponent’s PROCESSOR AREA.

I take this to mean any algae that roll pass the sensor will score for the alliance that owns those sensors.  So if you score in the wrong processor, the OTHER alliance will get the 6 points.

You get 6 points

Your opponents get a chance for the human player to shoot for 4 points

Net points: 2

Your opponent gets 6 points

Your human player may get a chance to shoot for 4 points (unless disallowed by some other rules)

Net points: -2

posts.name: Fletch
posts.cooked:
stephen.ostermiller:

I take this to mean any algae that roll pass the sensor will score for the alliance that owns those sensors

While I agree this is likely the intent, I’ve seen nothing in the rules clarifying it.  Unlike past years (and even other field elements this year), theres zero color-coding for the PROCESSOR other than the Human Player zone tape.  The front HDPE is black vs red/blue, and there is no field-side tape around it.

I think this is where the confusion is, and will probably be Q&A Q1
